Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.62,0:01:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.33,0:01:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the police! Open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.17,0:02:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light of summer is the radiance of yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.88,0:02:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the aftermath of the tears lies a two-hour special.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.84,0:02:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During a long three day vacation, we have two cases to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.59,0:02:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the Detective Koushien!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.93,0:02:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brain of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.76,0:02:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.15,0:03:50.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(800,250)\an\1c&HFEFFFE&\4c&HB6BCBE&\}Three days with Heiji Hattori
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.75,0:03:59.10,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&HD0ACDB&\bord2\blur3}Light Pink\N{\xbord3}Cherry Blossom Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.96,0:04:02.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What pretty cherry tress!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.33,0:04:06.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Sure are! This is such a lively Sakura\Nfestival. Aren't you glad we came?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.25,0:04:08.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Thanks, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.54,0:04:17.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Speaking of thanks, who rushed to pick up some high schoolers\Nfrom Osaka and drive them like mad here for the flower viewing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was me, Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, was it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.52,0:04:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.18,0:04:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.81,0:04:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even in the midst of it, instead of thanking me, it looks\Nlike those guys are more interested in the dango than the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.23,0:04:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? Wasn't Heiji the one\Nwho wanted to come flower viewing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.53,0:04:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't these pinwheels cute?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.24,0:04:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sure are! I'm buying one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.95,0:04:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How much, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.45,0:04:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're 200Â¥.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.75,0:04:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll take one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what're you so dazed by?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.60,0:05:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you call me because you wanted me to do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was about some high schooler with glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.52,0:05:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right, right. Hondou Eisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a second year high school student. It\Nseems he's in the same class as Ran now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.86,0:05:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want you to check on something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.37,0:05:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that guy have something to do with Osaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I want you to check out the one\Nwho has the same eyes as Hondou Eisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.33,0:05:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A colleague of those men in black,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.25,0:05:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mizunashi Rena?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.51,0:05:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the announcer on Nichiuri TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think she's on vacation now, though.\NYou're saying she's one of those bad guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.43,0:05:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.89,0:05:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lower your voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's on vacation because she was badly injured\Nin a bike accident while the FBI was pursuing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.86,0:05:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, she's at a hospital in a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.57,0:06:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? How do I fit in?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.74,0:06:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want something checked out, wouldn't it be\Nbetter to ask that skinny detective, Takagi, or whatever?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.71,0:06:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.04,0:06:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A picture, taken at least 10 years ago, that coincidentally shows a girl\Nwho looks exactly like Mizunashi Rena was put up on a website briefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.34,0:06:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was carrying a bag from an convenience\Nstore, with Tsuutenkaku Tower in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.38,0:06:27.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If that's true, that'd mean she lived in Osaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:29.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I haven't made any conclusions yet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.27,0:06:36.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,When someone took it to the TV station to confirm if it was\Nauthentic, a few days later the site it was posted on was shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It makes you think something's going on, doesn't is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.86,0:06:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I want you to hurry and check it out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.66,0:06:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you can quietly look into that girl, I\Ncan get a step ahead of Hondou Eisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.95,0:06:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if that's the case, why don't you investigate here instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:06:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to catch this Hondou guy,\Nwouldn't approaching him directly be faster?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.17,0:07:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they look alike and really are related, that would\Nmean he could be in league with the bad guys as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's probably not with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.39,0:07:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's strange, but the way Hondou Eisuke behaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.06,0:07:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's great to meet you, Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.02,0:07:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.69,0:07:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, it looks like there was no wound to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.23,0:07:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He appears to be a genuine transfer student.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.82,0:07:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that would mean the one\Nwith the same eyes, Mizunashi Rena is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a colleague of those guys in black...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who murdered Hondou Eisuke's sister and with plastic surgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.67,0:07:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was simply able to take her place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, please have Inspector Ohtaki look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.30,0:07:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make sure he's careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have him see if a woman named\NMizunashi or Hondou ever lived in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.39,0:07:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.35,0:07:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If such a woman was really there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.85,0:07:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if, after some unknown time, there's a\Nrecord of her disappearance, it'd be a 'bingo', right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.94,0:07:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.94,0:07:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She really did!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.02,0:08:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as if the gods spirited her away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be some sort of sign for me to run\Ninto a famous detective such as yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.86,0:08:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you, could you please solve this mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.33,0:08:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This monk suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.29,0:08:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.17,0:08:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.25,0:08:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm an apprentice at that temple and my name is Denkyuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.84,0:08:28.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A few days ago, a guest came and visited the head monk...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.84,0:08:31.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly disappeared from her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:31.82,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(450,450)}\h\h\hDenkyuu (18)\h\h\h\N{\fs9}\hShougaku Temple Disciple\h
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.31,0:08:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.52,0:08:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guest was a long-haired woman who\Nhad come to stay at the temple for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:44.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I went to tell her that breakfast was ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.95,0:08:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.86,0:08:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't she have just gone home before breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, when I went to the guest room she was staying in...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.29,0:08:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had a knife stuck in her stomach and\Nwasn't breathing! It was a horrible sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.08,0:09:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying she was dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.75,0:09:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.17,0:09:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you tell that to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.55,0:09:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.76,0:09:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went right away to the head monk, who was asleep in the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.30,0:09:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when you said she 'disappeared'...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.68,0:09:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the police arrived, I lead them to the\Ndetached shrine to find the head monk there, alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.56,0:09:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not even a shadow remained!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.90,0:09:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman's body and even the\Nblood on the tatami mats had disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.20,0:09:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.24,0:09:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then? What did the head monk say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.24,0:09:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He said she had left earlier that\Nmorning and that I had just dream it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.58,0:09:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you weren't just half asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.87,0:09:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.46,0:09:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely saw it, with my own eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.50,0:09:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.88,0:09:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're so sure, why don't we go to\Nthe temple and talk to the head monk?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you're the famous Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.96,0:09:58.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Such a famous detective as yourself, coming to such a small mountain temple...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:09:59.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why have you come?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:59.75,CharCard02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}\hShakuren (57)\h\N{\fs11}\h\hShougaku Temple\h\h\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHead Monk\h\h\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.40,0:10:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of your Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.44,0:10:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, perhaps this is about my guest\Nwho supposedly disappeared like the mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're interested in his dream story, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.12,0:10:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.62,0:10:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, to be blunt, we came to see whether,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.62,0:10:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What this monk saw was an illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.71,0:10:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or whether someone actually died and you\Nsecretly cleaned up the body before the police came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.84,0:10:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.26,0:10:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what an interesting young man you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.10,0:10:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.10,0:10:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go visit the detached shrine, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.65,0:10:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To see the room that Denkyuu claims can swallow a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.99,0:10:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, it's a long way to get to this detached shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.29,0:11:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, the temple we were just in looks so far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.00,0:11:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.75,0:11:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.54,0:11:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.25,0:11:09.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This building looks pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.76,0:11:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, because it was built some fifty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.77,0:11:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, come inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.27,0:11:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each room contains eight mats,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.35,0:11:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making four rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.15,0:11:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well? Where was that woman's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.49,0:11:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the upper right corner of this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right about there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.99,0:11:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.70,0:11:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.91,0:11:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem these tatami mats are two-sided.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, a Buddhist statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.79,0:11:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Niou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.21,0:11:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's one of the four heavenly kings, Tamonten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.34,0:11:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this room, which faces north, is Tamonten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,West is Koumokuten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,South is Zoujouten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.14,0:11:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And east is Jikokuten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.27,0:12:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how each statue is placed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.73,0:12:05.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't mind if you touch them, but please do not damage them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.65,0:12:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are valuable Buddhist statues of this\NShougaku temple that have been passed down for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.49,0:12:15.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's become quite late now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.16,0:12:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not stay here at the temple for the night and\Ncontinue investigating in the morning when it becomes light?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.33,0:12:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's only if you say that you haven't searched enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.13,0:12:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You really want to stay at the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.09,0:12:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surely that monk was just half-asleep and made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.76,0:12:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that's the case, let's head back to Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.14,0:12:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.02,0:12:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That woman's body is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.65,0:12:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time she's right in the middle of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.86,0:12:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it in the same room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.66,0:12:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the exact same one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.91,0:13:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.75,0:13:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.25,0:13:08.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really just...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:10.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected, when you tell someone, it disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.38,0:13:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Head Monk...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.13,0:13:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, that day, no guest came to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.01,0:13:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were probably chasing the shadow\Nof your mother who passed away long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.81,0:13:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.56,0:13:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:45.25,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&H20258D&\bord2\blur4}Red\NDisappeared Bloodstain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.06,0:13:42.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I really saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:49.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As I just said, it's an illusion brought\Nforth by a heart that yearns for his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.75,0:13:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.13,0:13:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eighteen years ago, that mother entrusted you to this\Ntemple and then threw herself into the sea in her grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Entrusted?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.59,0:13:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.64,0:14:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Denkyuu is the foundling child I have raised for\N18 years, ever since I accepted the job of head monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.52,0:14:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I cannot refuse anyone, such is my nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.15,0:14:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two or three others were entrusted to us as well, but\Nthey weren't suited to temple life and have departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.53,0:14:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after being apart so long,\NDenkyuu can't forget about his dear mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.08,0:14:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Head Monk, you mean to say that the\Nwoman's body Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, no guests came that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.84,0:14:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, on that morning three days\Nago, after I saw Denkyuu so shaken up...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.05,0:14:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought perhaps someone did get lost in the\Nmountains and wound up in the detached shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.64,0:14:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I could find no one, just like tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.35,0:14:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I pity Denkyuu for having to see such an illusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.98,0:15:01.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the police came, knowing what I knew, I simply\Ntold them the woman guest had left earlier that morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.62,0:15:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, does that solve the mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.41,0:15:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.08,0:15:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.54,0:15:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a woman in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.17,0:15:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if it was only briefly, three days\Nago Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.17,0:15:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Head Monk, does Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlike to dress up in women's clothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.43,0:15:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Women's clothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.10,0:15:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.93,0:15:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because I found this in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.39,0:15:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.85,0:15:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a pierced earring clasp?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.69,0:15:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earlier this evening, when we were checking if the\Ntatami mats were two-sided or not, this boy came across it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This earring clasp was all by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning it most likely came off and\Nfell below when the mats were moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.62,0:15:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the only question is: Whose earring is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:58.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shiny earring clasp went unnoticed\Nbecause it was in a place the sun didn't shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.59,0:16:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.97,0:16:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman I saw three days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.43,0:16:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was wearing a pierced earring!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, please explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.97,0:16:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If what Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw was an illusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably left by one of those\Ntwo that served here until two months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.32,0:16:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bunkyuu or Rinkyuu, one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.03,0:16:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bunkyuu and Rinkyuu?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I just tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.41,0:16:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Other children aside from Denkyuu have been left here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.29,0:16:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike Denkyuu, those two were always troublesome kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.79,0:16:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Night after night they would sneak out of the temple to visit the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.67,0:16:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They disguised themselves so they wouldn't be recognized as monks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.34,0:16:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disguised?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.80,0:16:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.72,0:16:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know where they got them,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they wore wigs, earrings, and casual clothes\Nin the modern style young people wear these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.39,0:16:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.77,0:16:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those two would hide in the shrine and drink alcohol too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.94,0:17:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the head monk found out, they got a good scolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.11,0:17:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they couldn't stand this temple anymore, they both left together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.16,0:17:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since those two used this shrine to change\Nclothes in, some things were probably left here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.71,0:17:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it is. You get all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.59,0:17:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your face tells me you're not happy with that explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.59,0:17:26.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to check around here again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.18,0:17:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's as Denkyuu says and a bloodstained woman's body\Nwas here, there should be some blood on the tatami mats, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.06,0:17:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:41.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't Heiji and the others kinda late?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.73,0:17:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.78,0:17:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if something happened over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.45,0:17:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here just in case, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.62,0:17:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.82,0:17:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, then I'll come too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.63,0:18:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, waiting here quietly would be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.05,0:18:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.34,0:18:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.91,0:18:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what location was that woman lying in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three days ago, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.41,0:18:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.17,0:18:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the woman you found just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.38,0:18:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the room, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a lot blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.38,0:18:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.55,0:18:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both three days ago and tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.55,0:18:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was quite a bit around the abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.35,0:18:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, nine times out of ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.02,0:19:00.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we exclude the body three days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.48,0:19:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the body you found tonight was really in that position,\Nthere should be blood on some of the tatami mats around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.82,0:19:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked all of the mats and found nothing at all, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.87,0:19:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.08,0:19:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As he said, I really was just seeing the phantom of my dead mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.38,0:19:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, does that satisfy you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.88,0:19:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Denkyuu, escort them to the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.97,0:19:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.97,0:19:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be worshipping the four heavenly\Nkings placed in these rooms for a moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.93,0:19:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To apologize for the small annoyance we've caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.14,0:19:44.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize for having you all out this late because of my foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.61,0:19:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.48,0:19:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, what were you doing in the shrine at that hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.15,0:19:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I always come to make sure the doors are shut before dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.70,0:20:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, cleaning up and locking the\Nshrine door had been Bunkyuu and Rinkyuu's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.79,0:20:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After they were caught drinking, the head\Nmonk took over the cleaning and I began locking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.92,0:20:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just alcohol, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.84,0:20:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two also smoked in there, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.72,0:20:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two said they cleaned thoroughly so they wouldn't get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.43,0:20:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter what, they couldn't clean the burn mark on one of the mats.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.56,0:20:27.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, I saw a beer stain too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.57,0:20:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I don't get why those two marks are there now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.65,0:20:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But weren't when we searched earlier this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.20,0:20:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you were going to say, right, Heiji-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.95,0:20:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.66,0:20:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't trying to say someone switched the mats around, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.29,0:20:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that would explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.92,0:20:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.42,0:20:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you two checked the mats in that\Nshrine, you should know they aren't double-sided.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.88,0:20:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, they're old and tanned from the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:21:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a new mat was brought in and placed somewhere,\Nthe color would be wrong and you would notice right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.56,0:21:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it were from inside, it'd be different, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.44,0:21:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the tatami mats could have\Nbeen moved from another of the four rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.57,0:21:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes about seven or eight minutes to get to the shrine from your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.95,0:21:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's more than enough time to switch the mats.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.87,0:21:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, something\Ndid feel different when we returned...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.62,0:21:25.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true? So, the mats really were different?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.46,0:21:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it was just a feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.88,0:21:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you moved the mats\Naround, you couldn't hide the blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.13,0:21:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the bloodstains were in the middle of the room,\Nat least two of the mats would have blood on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.60,0:21:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those four heavenly king statues in the\Ncorners of the rooms were also strange, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.81,0:21:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're in cases made of glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.48,0:21:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you take out the statues, you can see the tatami\Nthrough the bottom, so hiding anything there is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:54.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, it's time to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.57,0:21:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of having this stupid conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.29,0:22:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mistake!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.79,0:22:06.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying the body was never there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.67,0:22:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was just this monk seeing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.63,0:22:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.84,0:22:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad. This means no one died.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.30,0:22:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then hurry and get in so we can go to Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.26,0:22:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that your pinwheel?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.68,0:22:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rats, I smashed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.26,0:22:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, at least it didn't get bent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.98,0:22:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.44,0:22:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was the burn mark not present\Nearlier but suddenly is now at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.90,0:22:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did we miss it because it was hidden?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.86,0:22:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.91,0:22:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Heiji-niichan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.45,0:22:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now you're doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.09,0:22:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it! This!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.67,0:22:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know where the blood is hidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.30,0:22:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.51,0:22:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.18,0:23:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.99,0:23:11.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.80,0:23:14.20,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&H3081AC&\bord2\blur4}Orange\NPinwheel Room
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.96,0:23:15.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So the woman I found both tonight and three days ago was real?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.20,0:23:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was no phantom, that really was a dead body.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.62,0:23:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was cleverly hidden to make it look like it had just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.88,0:23:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of a fantastic device.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.34,0:23:26.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A device?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.42,0:23:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what kind of device was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.84,0:23:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell us, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.39,0:23:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hint was this pinwheel. I figured it out when I saw this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.60,0:23:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how you got it as well, right, Brat-from-Osaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.19,0:23:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.69,0:23:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why had the body disappeared when\NDenkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought us back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.61,0:23:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This pinwheel is like that detached shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:23:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That shrine has no railings, and it's\Nsquare-shaped with 4 rooms with 8 mats each.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.12,0:23:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Railings?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.62,0:23:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Square-shaped?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.00,0:23:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.16,0:24:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The incompetent detective brat\Nfrom Osaka doesn't quite get it yet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.13,0:24:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this is your deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.63,0:24:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, the shrine was rotated 180 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.89,0:24:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, I don't think there's a device like that in the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.77,0:24:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course you wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.56,0:24:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, it was built fifty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.31,0:24:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, when the police searched three days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.52,0:24:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when you all searched tonight, after I brought you here,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.65,0:24:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We completely searched each of the four rooms, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.82,0:24:36.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we didn't find a body or blood in any of the rooms, did we?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.95,0:24:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.91,0:24:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.33,0:24:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a building was built like today's amusement parks fifty years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.88,0:24:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been a big tourist attraction around here, you moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.42,0:24:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there wasn't a body then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.47,0:24:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were just hallucinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.89,0:24:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there was both a body and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.18,0:25:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't see it because it was hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.48,0:25:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was hidden?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.90,0:25:06.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mind telling us where?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.19,0:25:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.07,0:25:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.32,0:25:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I slipped trying to pick up the badge I dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.74,0:25:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.66,0:25:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was raining since this morning and\Nit looks like it's still muddy in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.58,0:25:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More importantly, is my Detective Badge lying around here anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.21,0:25:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.88,0:25:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, for starters...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.51,0:25:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here are your glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.76,0:25:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.26,0:25:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found the badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.97,0:25:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.05,0:25:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.30,0:25:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't there when I looked a second ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.81,0:25:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.81,0:25:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, maybe it's because of this leaf sticking to my glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.40,0:25:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, like this, you can see the badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.86,0:25:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you put down these glasses\Nwith a leaf on them, you can't see it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.70,0:25:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, it blends in with the leaves scattered on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.66,0:26:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't see the badge at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.00,0:26:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, perhaps this is the same trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.37,0:26:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.58,0:26:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say 'trick'?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.42,0:26:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you can hide the blood using this same trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.26,0:26:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Underneath cases of the four heavenly kings\Nstatues in the corners of the rooms in that shrine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.55,0:26:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't see anything under the cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.27,0:26:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After taking out the statues, you can see the\Ntatami mats underneath through the transparent bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.02,0:26:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.02,0:26:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you cut out a piece of the tatami and stick it to the bottom\Nof the glass case, and place it over the bloodstain on the mat,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.78,0:26:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It completely hides the blood and the glass case still seems transparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.03,0:26:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.33,0:26:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wouldn't anyone that picks up\Nthe cases discover the trick right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.25,0:26:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.75,0:26:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you pick the case up with the statue in it,\Nthe statue may tip over and break the glass case.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.63,0:26:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, by just picking up the statues, you'll see\Nwhat you believe is the unaltered tatami below.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.72,0:27:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely no one would bother to move the cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.22,0:27:05.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And naturally, none of us even thought to move the cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.60,0:27:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, why would anyone set all of that up?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.48,0:27:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would a murderer do all that just to hide the blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.40,0:27:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably originally done by the two\Nmonks who left the temple two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.07,0:27:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to hide the alcohol stain and the burn mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.29,0:27:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must have gone searching for\Ntatami the same color as the mats in the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.87,0:27:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And glued it to the bottoms of the statue cases, and placed the\Ncases on top of the stain and burn mark so they wouldn't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.96,0:27:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two were in charge of cleaning that shrine\Nand bragged about hiding all of that, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.47,0:27:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.10,0:27:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we didn't see the stains when\Nwe investigated the shrine this evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.14,0:27:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they were suddenly there when we investigated tonight\Nafter Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told us he saw the body again is the proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.69,0:27:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.94,0:28:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying those two monks secretly\Ncame back to the shrine and killed some woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.70,0:28:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, all those two did was set that trick up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.04,0:28:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who used the trick was the\None saw through it and scolded them for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.67,0:28:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head monk, Shakuren. Who else could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.46,0:28:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head monk?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.01,0:28:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying he killed that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.93,0:28:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.43,0:28:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had killed her, he wouldn't have left the body there three\Ndays ago for Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to find and returned to the temple to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.77,0:28:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman most likely committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.44,0:28:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told him a woman was\Ndead in the shrine, it occurred to him right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.65,0:28:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make it seem that Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was\Nseeing things and that there was never a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.07,0:28:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.45,0:28:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman's blood was in the right spot on the\Nmats, just like the alcohol and cigarette stains were.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.50,0:28:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used the trick with the cases, cleverly moving the\Nmats around and placing the cases on top to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.71,0:29:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And where did he put the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.88,0:29:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably hid it under the floor of\Nthe shrine, or at least until the police left.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.85,0:29:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the body I saw tonight was the\Nsame as the one from three days ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.23,0:29:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the body you saw tonight was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.85,0:29:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head monk lying down, dressed as a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.11,0:29:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head monk?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.86,0:29:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he probably wore one of the wigs those two monks left behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.20,0:29:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And ketchup for the blood with a knife held to his stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.54,0:29:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought that if the same thing happened\Ntwice, both we and Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.62,0:29:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman's body was a hallucination and would move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.13,0:29:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.09,0:29:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, the statues in the\Nshrine were placed in the four corners of the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.97,0:29:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either in the upper right or lower left corner of a mat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.18,0:29:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stains those two monks tried to hide with the cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.93,0:29:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were two stains from a cigarette burn and alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.60,0:29:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the blood from the body three days ago could be hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.73,0:30:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood from the corpse Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nsaw today was in the middle of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.16,0:30:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means there were four bloodstained mats.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.41,0:30:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think the blood from tonight\Ncould be hidden with just two cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.04,0:30:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he used four cases, not just two.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.17,0:30:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The priest copied those two and did the\Nsame trick with the two remaining cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.46,0:30:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way could hide four places.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.80,0:30:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tonight, he used the two originally\Nbloodstained mats and two other mats.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.64,0:30:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stained the top of the 4 mats with something that looked like blood,\Nand lay down in the middle of the room like the woman's corpse was.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.69,0:30:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He pretended he was dead and waited for Denkyuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to show.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.98,0:30:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he got scared by the corpse and went to get\Nus, he hid the bloodstained mats in the four corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.61,0:30:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he showed up behind us as we came to\Nthe shrine and acted like nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.99,0:30:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the head monk laid down like the corpse in the center of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.17,0:31:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the fake blood stains wouldn't be on the corners of the mats.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.92,0:31:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with four cases, it would be impossible to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.01,0:31:07.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.18,0:31:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see! The bloodstains could have been\Nwhere the corners of the mats came together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.64,0:31:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the blood would be same places in the upper-right and lower-left,\Nand on the remaining two it would be in the upper-left and lower-right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.07,0:31:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.36,0:31:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Ah, the other way. That way there are two in the upper-left,\Nso no problem. As I thought, there are two in the upper-left still.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.71,0:31:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The statues are in the four corners of the\Nrooms, so you can't hide all four mats, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.59,0:31:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are those the only ways to arrange them?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.72,0:31:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.05,0:31:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.85,0:31:55.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a pinwheel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.35,0:31:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.56,0:32:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you arranged the mats like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.94,0:32:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the blood is always in the upper right corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.52,0:32:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.78,0:32:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I sensed something was strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.94,0:32:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrangement of the tatami mats was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.78,0:32:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would the head monk go to so much trouble to hide the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.24,0:32:17.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body of some woman who committed suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.54,0:32:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we just ask him directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.75,0:32:38.70,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&H0F0D0C&\bord3\blur4}Black\NMonk's confession
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.71,0:32:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, why did the head monk do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.97,0:32:45.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did he try to hide it so much and even pretend to be the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.01,0:32:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if they found the corpse, the\Nwoman's identity would be discovered?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.93,0:32:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't want the woman's identity to be known?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.68,0:32:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was she?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.16,0:33:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you seem to have returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.24,0:33:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I wasn't able to keep hiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.83,0:33:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.29,0:33:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're ten million years too young\Nto deceive the eyes of Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.71,0:33:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I must ask Denkyuu to\Nleave before I can answer your questions-
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.47,0:33:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already told him to return to the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.05,0:33:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked him to make sure the girls didn't get lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.60,0:33:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you had him in mind, the woman who\Nkilled herself three days ago must have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.73,0:33:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was the woman who, eighteen years ago,\Nabandoned Denkyuu in front of this temple in a cardboard box.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.20,0:33:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Denkyuu's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.57,0:33:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.37,0:33:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.41,0:33:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She appeared suddenly in the evening\Nthree days ago, asking that we return her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.75,0:34:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She even claimed she had visited\Nevery year, watching over him as he grew.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.84,0:34:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I decided to show her an album with\Npictures of all of the monks that had served here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.09,0:34:14.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, as I feared, she couldn't pick out her son and broke into tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.06,0:34:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't even recognized that her son\Nwas the one who brought the album to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.73,0:34:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After I had Denkyuu retire, I felt compelled to scold her harshly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.24,0:34:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said, "Cool your head in the separate shrine for the night."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.36,0:34:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Experience the eighteen years of grief you\Nbrought on your son, down to your bones."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.45,0:34:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as dawn broke, I found her in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.71,0:34:41.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it would be too painful for Denkyuu to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.84,0:34:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I came up with this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.35,0:34:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess we should be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.89,0:34:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind driving me to the police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.44,0:34:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:35:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess after doing something like that, I\Nshouldn't have the right to say this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.57,0:35:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you plan to continue being a\Ndetective and using words to entrap people,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.12,0:35:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inscribe this in your hearts: Words are like knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.00,0:35:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When used incorrectly, they turn into foul weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.58,0:35:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to understand the\Nopponent's heart and use them with discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.67,0:35:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter who it is you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.72,0:35:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, why did the head monk hide the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.94,0:35:38.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah! Don't be stingy, hurry and tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.77,0:35:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji! C'mon, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.73,0:35:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji-
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.03,0:35:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.28,0:35:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I just say I didn't want to talk about it, moron?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.41,0:35:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his case, I have a feeling he puts all\Nhis strength into using words incorrectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.57,0:36:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it's already past 9:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.49,0:36:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he must have been out\Npartying last night and come home late.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.32,0:36:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How fortunate that it's Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.04,0:36:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected, it looks like Hattori and Kazuha left early.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.75,0:36:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're leaving early in the morning, so I'm off to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.34,0:36:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he said he would.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.84,0:36:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that guy, does he even remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.26,0:36:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he promised to look into Mizunashi Rena?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.47,0:36:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll e-mail him later...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.60,0:36:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, its empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.35,0:36:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. I'll loan you mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.89,0:36:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.52,0:37:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you still here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.32,0:37:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you were leaving early!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.94,0:37:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I planned to, but with that old man's snoring...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.28,0:37:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't get enough sleep. Thanks to him, that plan's messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.41,0:37:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why aren't you hurrying to exchange tickets?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.79,0:37:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK, I'm not going home yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.59,0:37:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.63,0:37:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? A deserted island?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.17,0:37:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going there after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.26,0:37:32.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, were going to go after the flower viewing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.35,0:37:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it a case or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.76,0:37:38.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, it's for a TV program.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.98,0:37:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, loudmouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.56,0:37:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is it OK to wait this late to go to the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.40,0:37:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it leave early?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.48,0:37:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, even if we leave now, we'll be there in plenty of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.78,0:37:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.78,0:37:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had wanted to get up early, I could have gotten there before them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.28,0:37:56.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And checked out the faces and\Ncharacters of the other guys who were invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.33,0:37:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People like me. High-school detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.62,0:38:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-High-school detectives?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.54,0:38:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.63,0:38:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nichiuri TV has gathered guys like that from all\Nover the country to see who's the best in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.76,0:38:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're advertising it as a Detective Koushien.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.97,0:38:21.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Detective Koushien?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.84,0:38:24.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's why I told him not to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.75,0:38:23.10,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&HA95536&\bord3\blur4}Blue\NBeyond the see
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.84,0:38:27.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd be an idiot to go like that, just because he was invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.30,0:38:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so too, but I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.64,0:38:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was right there in the invitation letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.23,0:38:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, Hattori Heiji, was invited as the representative from the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.73,0:38:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The West?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.19,0:38:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since the West is me, the East is obviously...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.15,0:38:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.45,0:38:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s face is red!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.62,0:38:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's just that it's a little warm today.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.70,0:38:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you don't think, that detective boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.00,0:38:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...might be coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.88,0:38:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.63,0:39:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As this guy well knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.84,0:39:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, do you two want to come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.34,0:39:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said there's lodging for any escorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.39,0:39:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows, maybe that conceited\Nhigh-school detective Kudou Shinichi will...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.27,0:39:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then again, we may find out otherwise, right, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.90,0:39:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hey. Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.86,0:39:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're late, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.90,0:39:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please try to be on time. We're\Ngetting underway in a matter of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.91,0:39:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry, somebody took the wrong road.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.51,0:39:37.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well, nevermind, let's head to the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.91,0:39:39.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Everyone else is already aboard the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.30,0:39:39.77,CharCard03,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}\h\h\h\hTsuchio Hiroo (41)\h\h\h\h\N{\fs13}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hNichiuri TV Director\h\h\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.79,0:39:42.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that means Shinichi's already here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.80,0:39:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou Shinichi, the high-school detective of the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.01,0:39:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I couldn't contact that young\Nman, so I don't know if he's coming or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.68,0:39:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.47,0:39:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.27,0:39:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was obvious enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.69,0:40:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is the place where escorts like us\Nare staying there on the deserted island?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.61,0:40:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, there's only an old lodge on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.07,0:40:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's guardians will be staying at a hotel for the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.28,0:40:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow when the filming's over, we'll come pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.87,0:40:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.08,0:40:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, would it be OK to take this kid with?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.41,0:40:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's kind of like my assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.62,0:40:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he stays in your room, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.55,0:40:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But look at this huge ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.97,0:40:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be there are people here from each of the 47 districts?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.55,0:40:35.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, we only invited four people,\Nfrom the East, West, South and North.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.10,0:40:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This ship was just an easy to find meeting place.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.18,0:40:41.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our ship is this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.40,0:40:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is our ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.52,0:40:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and board, time's getting short.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.03,0:40:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.32,0:40:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.57,0:40:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know that director guy from Nichiuri TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.12,0:40:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this is my first time meeting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.41,0:41:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've noticed his Nichiuri TV staff jumper, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.59,0:41:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.13,0:41:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the Kansai representative, you'd\Nbetter win! Or I'll never forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.47,0:41:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I won't be left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.01,0:41:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori Heiji is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.39,0:41:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to this, when we arrive on the\Nisland, you should stay in your rooms until dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.40,0:41:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And things will start after dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.15,0:41:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please be ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.78,0:41:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we arrive at the island, the competition will have begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.28,0:41:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.57,0:41:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Statement understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.78,0:41:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.41,0:41:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would expect them to be more excited about this Detective Koushien.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.08,0:41:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why'd you bring me along?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.46,0:41:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You better not be thinking I'm gonna help you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.59,0:41:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.01,0:41:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, since the East's Kudou Shinichi cant come.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.05,0:42:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just thought I should give you a\Nchance to compete, or else I'll win too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.64,0:42:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only real competition for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.48,0:42:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why you asked Ran and the other to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.52,0:42:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's was your stupid plan, since I couldn't come alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.45,0:42:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you getting seasick?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.12,0:42:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, it's just a hangover.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.08,0:42:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the recording was finished\Nyesterday, I drank too much with the staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.05,0:42:34.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you went over the top?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.88,0:42:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The top?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.01,0:42:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well, it was at a high-cost place.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.81,0:42:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.02,0:42:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Won't you at least laugh for me? You're so small-minded.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.89,0:42:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Laugh? Small-minded?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.31,0:42:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that pun between "high-cost" and "top" just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.28,0:42:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, those two, they're not too bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.70,0:42:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.66,0:42:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Koushien?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.95,0:43:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nichiuri TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.95,0:43:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't have any reservations for anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.75,0:43:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, check again.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.12,0:43:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It should include dinner and breakfast too.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.84,0:43:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.34,0:43:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.63,0:43:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.62,0:43:29.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Welcome. I'm the one appointed to look\Nafter you, Kouya Renzou. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.08,0:43:32.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shall we head directly to the lodge?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.71,0:43:32.10,CharCard04,,0,0,0,,{\fad(420,420)}\h\h\hKouya Renzou (58)\h\h\h\N{\fs13}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOfficial Caretaker\h\h\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.77,0:43:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Director{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.94,0:43:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like the high-school detective of the East hasn't come, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.57,0:43:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What shall we do about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.49,0:43:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.99,0:43:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.99,0:43:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the boy representing the East, he was\Nhere early this morning and is already at the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.29,0:43:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.38,0:43:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.21,0:43:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.80,0:44:07.28,Xtitle001,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs14\fad(500,0)}Subject: To my dear housekeeper\Nplease cancel tomorrow's\Ndinner reservations.\NIt seems I won't be back home\Nfor a while.\NI will definitely make up for it\Nsome later day.\N\N-Saguru
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.01,0:44:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. We're completely isolated from\Nthe outside world. Quite the solitary island.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.60,0:44:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For this scene of the mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.85,0:44:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the perfect situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.19,0:44:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha-Hakuba Saguru?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.32,0:44:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.42,0:44:30.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well now, can you high school\Ndetectives from the East, West, South and North.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.66,0:44:30.20,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&HF1F9F4&\bord0.5\blur5}White\NHighschool Detective in East
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.71,0:44:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please introduce yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.50,0:44:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.79,0:44:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.84,0:44:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without any TV cameras around?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.59,0:44:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there aren't any TV staff here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.34,0:44:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the crew and hosting talent aren't\Nscheduled to arrive until tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.72,0:44:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We brought you here earlier to get acquainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.35,0:44:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.82,0:44:52.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Koshimizu Natsuki, a third year high-school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.88,0:44:56.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I was born in Fukuoka and for now\NI'm the representative from the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.83,0:45:00.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I haven't even solved 100 cases yet, so I'm still a novice.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.87,0:44:57.63,CharCard05,,0,0,0,,{\fad(470,470)}Koshimizu Natsuki (18)\N{\fs13}\h\h\hHigh-School Detectives\h\h\h\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfrom the South\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.24,0:45:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't be too rough on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.99,0:45:04.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This one is Tokitsu Junya.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.37,0:45:10.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Though I was born in Tokyo, I grew up in\NHokkaido, so I'm the North's representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.63,0:45:16.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I've handled approximately 300 cases, where\Nmore than 250 people were arrested and prosecuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.34,0:45:10.81,CharCard06,,0,0,0,,{\fad(470,470)}\h\h\hTokitsu Junya (18)\h\h\h\N{\fs13}\h\h\hHigh-School Detectives\h\h\h\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfrom the North\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.25,0:45:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've had some cases where they got away or committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.01,0:45:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Hattori Heiji, a pretty well-known detective from the Kansai region.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.64,0:45:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for how many cases I've solved...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.43,0:45:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.85,0:45:34.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, it's more than 1,000, so it's hard to count them individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.69,0:45:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1-1,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.81,0:45:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.11,0:45:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, quit it with the nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.65,0:45:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, even if I may have included searching for cats as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.62,0:45:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so you're Hattori Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.20,0:45:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father speaks well of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.58,0:45:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said you're a very perceptive detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.75,0:45:55.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.79,0:45:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How does your dad know about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.34,0:46:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just like you, Heiji-niichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.55,0:46:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.51,0:46:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so, Hakuba-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.50,0:46:06.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, my father is a police commissioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.68,0:46:12.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Strangely, since your father is the director general of the\NOsaka Prefectural police, our circumstances are very similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.78,0:46:11.24,CharCard07,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}\hHakuba Saguru (18)\h\N{\fs13}\hHigh-School Detectives\h\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hfrom the East\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.60,0:46:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, how many cases have you solved?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.65,0:46:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see. I would say around 500?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.15,0:46:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, that's only half as many as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.15,0:46:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but then again, I'm only talking\Nabout the cases that occurred in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.74,0:46:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.16,0:46:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been studying abroad in England for awhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.66,0:46:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't come back to Japan often.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.46,0:46:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My old housekeeper has been accepting cases for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.38,0:46:43.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's quite unexpected. That someone who's famous\Noverseas like Hakuba would be the representative from the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.38,0:46:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was sure it'd be Kudou Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.26,0:46:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.34,0:46:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The high-school detective from the East is Kudou.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.10,0:46:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.48,0:46:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was my housekeeper, you see, who\Nreceived the call from the director here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.23,0:47:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked that I participate as the representative from\Nthe East to replace Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who could not be contacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.32,0:47:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the term replacement hurt my dear housekeeper's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.82,0:47:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The world should know that Hakuba is the\Nrepresentative from the East," she told me in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.00,0:47:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could I do? I zipped back from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.79,0:47:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it would seem I'm not an\Nappropriate representative for the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.34,0:47:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.88,0:47:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.55,0:47:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take the role of "guest from abroad,"
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.68,0:47:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And let Edogawa Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} here be the East's representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.77,0:47:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This boy is surprisingly good at deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.90,0:47:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he's even better than that Kudou Whoever{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.19,0:47:43.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling 'whoever'?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.07,0:47:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he's just a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.78,0:47:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's fine. It works for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.24,0:47:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More importantly, where are our rooms? I'm kinda tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.28,0:47:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.45,0:47:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.08,0:47:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is making dinner now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.96,0:48:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll call for you when it's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.54,0:48:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, one last thing. I want to check\Nyour clothes for the recording tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.42,0:48:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll call you on the phone when dinner's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.26,0:48:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wear clothes appropriate for the Detective Koushien.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.80,0:48:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.22,0:48:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no such project?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.22,0:48:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.98,0:48:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I asked around the station, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.40,0:48:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone said they'd never heard of a 'Detective Koushien'.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.07,0:48:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure that guy was from Nichiuri TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.11,0:48:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was wearing the station's\Nstaff jumper and I think his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.37,0:48:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio Hiroo.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.87,0:48:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.83,0:48:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no such director?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.33,0:48:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.83,0:48:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means they were taken by...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.33,0:48:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.42,0:48:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.59,0:48:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's your Detective Koushien outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.38,0:48:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I only wear this outfit at school and to ceremonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.18,0:48:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know, I was surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.97,0:48:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you knew that annoying guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.14,0:48:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Hakuba Saguru?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.93,0:49:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We met before on a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.94,0:49:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really think he's that annoying?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.02,0:49:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, looking down on others and talking trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.28,0:49:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kinda like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.61,0:49:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.90,0:49:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, you have more of an innocent child-like charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.78,0:49:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.91,0:49:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, from now on, we're mutual enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.62,0:49:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens, no consulting with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.92,0:49:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.96,0:49:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Dinner has been made\Nready, so please come to the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.01,0:49:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, this lodge is pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.72,0:49:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many places where it been repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.47,0:49:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's the owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.10,0:49:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows. I've heard the lodge is being rented\Ncheaply by some rich owner who no longer uses it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.90,0:49:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, has she already gone to the dining room?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.36,0:49:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.49,0:49:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm just about to call her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.57,0:49:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a woman on the island too?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.57,0:49:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's been with us from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.91,0:49:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.46,0:50:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dinner is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.58,0:50:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already time?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.71,0:50:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, I've been relaxing too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.17,0:50:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy's... a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.55,0:50:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My school regulations are very strict.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.97,0:50:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Skirt: 3 cm below the knees!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.68,0:50:17.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scarf: Bilaterally symmetrical!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.18,0:50:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Socks: Black!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.35,0:50:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perms are forbidden, shaving your eyebrows is a suspension.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.56,0:50:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how many times have I been\Nwarned about my naturally brown hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.73,0:50:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the cameras aren't here yet tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.23,0:50:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So whatever works is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.23,0:50:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.40,0:50:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.65,0:50:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not changing clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.90,0:50:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.90,0:50:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike you all, students in England can wear casual clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.83,0:50:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, looks delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.66,0:50:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made all of this, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.71,0:50:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.62,0:50:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's the director?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.67,0:50:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he didn't answer when I went to his room\Na while ago, so I assumed he'd be already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.47,0:50:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you please show us to his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.55,0:51:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}? Dinner's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.18,0:51:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.52,0:51:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, I guess he locked it so he could sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.53,0:51:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.49,0:51:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's blood on the knob!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.91,0:51:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a master key?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.78,0:51:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there aren't any keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.66,0:51:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like your rooms, you can only lock them from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.50,0:51:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's like our rooms, there must be two windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.87,0:51:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let's check from the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.67,0:51:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.09,0:51:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.77,0:51:48.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.55,0:51:49.38,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.41,0:51:50.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The window bolt...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.27,0:51:52.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.82,0:51:52.10,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&H1D2724&\bord2\blur3}Gray\NHighschool Detective in North
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.68,0:51:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the door was locked properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.60,0:51:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, this is a locked room murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.77,0:51:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.81,0:52:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be, if he were actually dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.32,0:52:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.94,0:52:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.78,0:52:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank God. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.66,0:52:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone knocked at the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.45,0:52:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I went out to check, there was no one there. Then when I was\Ngoing back into my room, someone suddenly drugged me from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.54,0:52:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Koushien: Case #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.75,0:52:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Solve the mystery of this locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.34,0:52:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you solve it, write down your\Ndeduction in a letter and quickly bring it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.55,0:52:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If your reasoning is correct, you'll advance to\Nround two and learn how to escape this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.19,0:52:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the battle's already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.31,0:52:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, does that mean there's a hidden camera somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.24,0:52:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.86,0:52:56.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought having us find out this guy\Nwas a fake director would be the first round.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.99,0:52:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about? I really am a Nichi-
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.79,0:53:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't try to play dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.29,0:53:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember when that guy said you went 'over the top'?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.83,0:53:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He meant that you over-did it by recording passed midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.55,0:53:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When this girl said "laugh for me" after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.09,0:53:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It meant to move something.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.43,0:53:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even an novice assistant director should know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.43,0:53:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way a director would not know those terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.69,0:53:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, the spiral eyeball on your Nichiuri TV mark is funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.19,0:53:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real one spins the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.99,0:53:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably how everyone knew you were a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.41,0:53:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this means we've broken into the first round, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.54,0:53:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but this one has passed you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.29,0:53:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've solved it...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.50,0:53:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This locked-room trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.67,0:53:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall I show you how it was done?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.46,0:53:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You solved it already?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.26,0:53:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so, please show us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.84,0:53:57.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.43,0:54:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you did, the others would know the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.56,0:54:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I said before, write down your\Ndeduction in a letter and bring it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.64,0:54:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must follow this rule throughout the first round.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.65,0:54:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is not the final round.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.48,0:54:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'm not telling it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.11,0:54:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the result will be the same whether it's the final round or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.41,0:54:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How self-confident you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.49,0:54:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care how the trick was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.04,0:54:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just wonder if Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't tie himself up after locking the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.63,0:54:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.92,0:54:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't the representative from the\NWest have noticed when he untied the rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.38,0:54:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how incompetent a detective he may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.76,0:54:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In-Incompetent?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.72,0:54:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was most unsatisfactory.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.89,0:54:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you discovered blood on the door\Nknob, you immediately smashed in the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.94,0:54:52.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that situation, it's best to check\Nthe situation inside from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.52,0:54:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you can decide whether to\Nsmash in the door or break the window glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.19,0:55:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were dead and leaning against the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.57,0:55:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would have destroyed potential\Nevidence when you smashed in the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.62,0:55:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-Idiot! How could I wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.54,0:55:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was eager to get to the crime scene before the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.29,0:55:14.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that disqualify him as a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.09,0:55:16.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.46,0:55:17.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's not unqualified.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.68,0:55:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.43,0:55:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji-niichan is simply hot-blooded!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.81,0:55:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.10,0:55:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this one will be going upstairs\Nto setup my room like this locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.60,0:55:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait for me while you enjoy your dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.15,0:55:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll take about one hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.28,0:55:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.65,0:55:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.65,0:55:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rom when Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} showed us our rooms to our\Ndiscovering the locked room case was about that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.41,0:55:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the trick took that long to set up?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.70,0:55:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.75,0:55:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'll tell you this just to be sure, this trick doesn't\Nrequire any foolish behavior from any violent detectives. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.09,0:56:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he won't repeat the same mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.59,0:56:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who made his name because his father is\Nthe famous Osaka Prefectural Police Director-General.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.47,0:56:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, representative from the West?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.10,0:56:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.81,0:56:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like hot detectives like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.19,0:56:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an9}Like I said, it was moored around\Nhere, a boat some children boarded!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.87,0:56:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an9}Do you know who's boat that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.11,0:56:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.36,0:56:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I've got a kinda bad feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.58,0:56:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No luck calling his cellphone?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.04,0:56:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I just keep getting an out-of-range message.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.04,0:56:34.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H0E54D2&\}The phone you have called is either in a location beyond\Nsignal range or can not be reached because it is not receiving power.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.42,0:56:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.67,0:56:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you don't feel something's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.80,0:56:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just have this feeling that something\Nhorrible is looming over Heiji and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.30,0:56:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're over reacting!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.93,0:56:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.76,0:56:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} will definitely be coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.52,0:56:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, it's still bothering me...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.60,0:56:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji's face before he left with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.52,0:56:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over and over, it keeps running through my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.82,0:57:00.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what about Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s cellphone?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.86,0:57:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.03,0:57:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no luck there either.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.57,0:57:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd feel a lot better if the representative\Nfrom the East, Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, was with Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.05,0:57:18.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H0E54D2&\}The phone you have called is either in a location beyond\Nsignal range or can not be reached because it is not receiving power.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.87,0:57:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't reach Shinichi's cellphone either.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.63,0:57:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that Shinichi's there too?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.75,0:57:40.05,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&HA12E72&\bord1\blur4}Purple\NScent or Lavender
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.25,0:57:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it, we're out of range.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.34,0:57:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this is an isolated island.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.97,0:57:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.01,0:57:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just go to the bathroom now it's all almost gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.76,0:57:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't eat so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.89,0:57:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.14,0:57:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez..
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.64,0:58:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, now that your stomach is\Nfull, will you talk to us, fake Director{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.98,0:58:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you lie about your position\Nand arrange in this 'Detective Koushien'?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.70,0:58:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it isn't to test our abilities, what is your job?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.95,0:58:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.95,0:58:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I told you, I wouldn't get my promised fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.87,0:58:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From Nichiuri TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.75,0:58:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, will you answer this?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.29,0:58:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's been bothering me since I got to this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.13,0:58:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the aroma of lavender everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.26,0:58:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, it was in our room too, wasn't it. Lavender.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.42,0:58:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.68,0:58:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My room, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.31,0:58:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like it's in every room.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.89,0:58:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, there was a toolbox next to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.77,0:58:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that means something, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.40,0:58:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.40,0:58:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finding that out is a task for you detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.74,0:58:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rest is up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.78,0:58:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.16,0:58:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I rather find out why we've been cut off from the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.83,0:59:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Lavender Mansion Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.84,0:59:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hearing "lavender" reminds me of a\Ncase that happened in Shikoku a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.34,0:59:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard about it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.72,0:59:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, the one who\Ndied was the young mistress of the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.28,0:59:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Young mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.45,0:59:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason, half a year later, they decided it was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.04,0:59:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.71,0:59:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard they committed suicide before they were apprehended.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.80,0:59:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.89,0:59:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.55,0:59:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot my cigarettes in my room.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.06,1:00:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really coming down.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.99,1:00:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you so wet?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.36,1:00:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you were looking for a cigarette vending machine outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.66,1:00:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, I just stepped outside for a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.91,1:00:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, don't you think he's a little late?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.87,1:00:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.87,1:00:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, it's been over two hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.96,1:00:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go ask how much longer it will be.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.55,1:00:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.38,1:00:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.47,1:00:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't in his room?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.84,1:00:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.51,1:00:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knocked a lot, but he didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.76,1:00:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door was locked, you don't think...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.60,1:00:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.77,1:00:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have already finished preparing the\Nlocked room and is off snickering somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.02,1:00:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, wouldn't he want to show his grinning face to all of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.94,1:00:55.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that's so, I'll check from outside. Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.82,1:00:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go too then.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.74,1:00:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would be worried if you went alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.99,1:01:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.25,1:01:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Isn't that him by the window?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.84,1:01:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now, isn't that blood?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.30,1:01:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quick, to his room!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.64,1:01:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.64,1:01:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.61,1:01:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you see, Hattori?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.28,1:01:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.49,1:01:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's really dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.71,1:01:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the situation?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.12,1:01:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, he was killed by a blow to the head.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.54,1:01:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder weapon must be that hammer, there's even blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.26,1:02:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably taken from that toolbox next to the lavender flowerpot.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.51,1:02:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the window lock?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.76,1:02:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was firmly locked until I broke it open.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.18,1:02:10.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the window frame is held by screws.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.69,1:02:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same with the door, no sign of any trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.32,1:02:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With no secret entrances, that means this really is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.32,1:02:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A locked room murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.11,1:02:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And moreover the criminal is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.74,1:02:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koshimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. It's one of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.33,1:02:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on now, boy...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.16,1:02:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why us?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.79,1:02:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.21,1:02:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokitsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} went to his room upstairs,\Nclaiming he would demonstrate the locked room trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.17,1:02:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of us were in the dining room on the\Nfirst floor and had started eating dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.51,1:02:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the bathroom, which took about 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.64,1:02:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A while after I returned, Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to his room to get cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.77,1:02:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to check on Tokitsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.90,1:02:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Hakuba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the other two were in the dinning\Nroom the whole time, what he said would make sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.86,1:02:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.07,1:03:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only came here because I was hired!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.45,1:03:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By whom? I don't think any TV channel\Nwould film something with people actually dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.62,1:03:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really thought it was a TV program!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.66,1:03:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is I'm in a small theater troupe.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.96,1:03:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got a letter from someone at Nichiuri TV asking,\N"Would you like to be a director for our channel?"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.63,1:03:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got 500,000 in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.30,1:03:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He promised another 500,000 if I wasn't uncovered as a fake.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.47,1:03:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who wouldn't jump at such a sweet deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.64,1:03:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? If we found out?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.06,1:03:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I was found out, I was to maintain it really was a\NDetective Koushien until the end and I'd still get half, 250,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.98,1:03:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought you said were going to your room for cigarettes?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.90,1:03:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead, you came back soaked. Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.07,1:03:46.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to use radio in the shed to call for emergency help.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.62,1:03:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.66,1:03:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had been broken!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.54,1:03:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know it was fine when I came here three days ago to prepare.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.50,1:03:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.62,1:03:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.42,1:03:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's strange...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.29,1:04:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you went to the shed, it was still before the murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.30,1:04:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you know an emergency would happen?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.34,1:04:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just felt something would happen...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.93,1:04:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.85,1:04:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}? Were you also called here like Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.19,1:04:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I came here two days ago to look after everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.15,1:04:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had just quit my job and left the house\Nwhere I had been employed as a butler.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.86,1:04:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you did know about the locked room trick, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.87,1:04:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You told us to write it down and hand it to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.03,1:04:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was instructed to say that when the "locked room" occurred.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.95,1:04:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also told to hide the solution under the bathroom mat.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.58,1:04:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Funny you should say it that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.46,1:04:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes it seem the mastermind is someone other than you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.00,1:04:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.92,1:04:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care about that, I'm just like the rest of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.34,1:04:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was called by this fake director to be the\Nrepresentative from the South and brought here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.64,1:04:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate thunder!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.35,1:04:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, close the window! Please!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.94,1:05:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.28,1:05:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.19,1:05:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of the thunder and the case for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.20,1:05:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this guy?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.20,1:05:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm going to look around.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.04,1:05:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You three suspects should wait in the dining room on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.29,1:05:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope you want me to be on alert with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.80,1:05:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you're so hot-blooded, or should I say uncivilized?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.14,1:05:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.51,1:05:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.26,1:05:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've scattered glass everywhere and\Ngot your muddy footprints on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.73,1:05:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a horrible situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.94,1:05:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you have carelessly touched the lock with your bare hands?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.36,1:05:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, to open it!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.02,1:05:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.28,1:05:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's he the one who's angry?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.86,1:05:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm disappointed in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.57,1:05:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father had me thinking you were a better detective than this.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.58,1:05:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, after I take them to the\Ndining room, I'll begin investigating again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.41,1:06:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try not to get in the way, representative from the West.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.21,1:06:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Kudou...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.71,1:06:06.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I in the wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.76,1:06:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.68,1:06:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Not at all?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.55,1:06:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a boat that a man with a moustache,\Nthree high-schoolers, and a kid got on board!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.52,1:06:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you not know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.35,1:06:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.98,1:06:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason, I'm sure, something was bothering him.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.44,1:06:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That time, with what Heiji said.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.15,1:06:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wont fall behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.57,1:06:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori Heiji is here!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.07,1:06:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji said 'here'. "Come here?"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.24,1:06:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, what Heiji said then.\NHe might have meant, "Come here."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.37,1:06:41.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.20,1:06:50.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There's one thing I don't get.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.75,1:06:51.05,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&H9B381A&\bord1\blur10}Blue, {\3c&HFFF4EB&}White {\3c&H888986&}and {\3c&H000000&}Black\N{\3c&H9B381A&}Each {\3c&HFFF4EB&}person's {\3c&H000000&}reasoning
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.14,1:06:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd the murderer bother to put\NTokitsu's body on the table by the window?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.31,1:06:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in this position.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.15,1:06:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does it mean something?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.44,1:07:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably just for the appeal of having us see this\Nlocked room murder from outside. That's how I see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.91,1:07:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's with the lavender and the tool boxes?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.53,1:07:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's room seem to have them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.92,1:07:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just looking it from the outside won't tell us anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.25,1:07:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's open it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.83,1:07:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.04,1:07:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.17,1:07:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.89,1:07:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wire, nails, wire cutters, a screwdriver, a drill, a\Nsquare, pliers, wood bond, a saw, a utility knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.19,1:07:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it. No hammer.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.61,1:07:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that means the murder weapon came from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.57,1:07:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using a hammer like this, the guy of course, the\Nwoman, or even the old man could have committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.37,1:07:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going by time, I can say those three were out of our vicinity as follows:
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.80,1:08:01.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Koshimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to the toilet between 19:26:32 and 19:39:15.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.17,1:08:09.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to get cigarettes from\Nhis room between 20:06:47 and 21:28:31.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.59,1:08:17.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Finally, Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to check on\NTokitsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} between 21:30:06 and 21:38:52.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.85,1:08:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three had the 10 minutes that\Nwould be needed to commit the crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.44,1:08:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He recorded the seconds?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.94,1:08:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was mostly in the kitchen and\Nout of our sight, so wasn't he able to move freely?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.49,1:08:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, all of the windows in the kitchen are fixed and can't be opened.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.37,1:08:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same with the skylight.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.58,1:08:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kitchen door is here. In other words, he couldn't have\Ngotten out without passing through the dining room where we were.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.29,1:08:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So most-likely Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was always in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.63,1:08:52.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, this is a rough sketch of the second floor. All four\Nrooms have windows that face slightly different directions.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.55,1:08:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they're furnished in roughly the same way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.39,1:08:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure work fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.68,1:09:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because I arrived a half-day ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.48,1:09:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, how do we have electricity here?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.73,1:09:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is a deserted island.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.78,1:09:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard there's a small generator in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.07,1:09:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we have a look?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.24,1:09:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The radio he mentioned is there as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.05,1:09:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.63,1:09:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really has been broken in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.64,1:09:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the generator, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.47,1:09:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place doesn't have a lock?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.68,1:09:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there should be a padlock.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.81,1:09:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} keeps the key.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.15,1:09:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The padlock...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.82,1:09:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone was forcing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.03,1:09:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at all these muddy footprints.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.83,1:10:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must be Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.45,1:10:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who went out after it began to rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.96,1:10:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Hakuba-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.04,1:10:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.67,1:10:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.46,1:10:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy vanished.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.59,1:10:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not here... Not here...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.80,1:10:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.43,1:10:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, the toolbox in that person's room..
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.89,1:10:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has no wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.06,1:10:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hakuba hasn't come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.19,1:10:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wasn't he with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.15,1:10:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, did you find anything? It\Nlooks like you went looking in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.32,1:10:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.82,1:10:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impossible, impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.41,1:10:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like this guy's drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.29,1:10:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may act like you're detectives, but\Nin the end your abilities come up short.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.12,1:10:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all just mere show.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.09,1:10:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, shall I'll let you hear my mere show of a deduction?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.72,1:11:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.26,1:11:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.27,1:11:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.35,1:11:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal is...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.48,1:11:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.73,1:11:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.90,1:11:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.86,1:11:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You murdered Tokitsu and then created the locked room scenario...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.62,1:11:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouya Renzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.67,1:11:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's quite simple when you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.29,1:11:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokitsu said he'd take one hour to\Nrecreate the locked room in his own room.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.30,1:11:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it's a time consuming trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.22,1:11:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely you went to see him just\Nas he was finishing his preparations.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.43,1:11:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And killed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.68,1:11:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then naturally you decided to use the already\Ncompleted trick to make it a locked room murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.15,1:11:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why neither Koshimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who went to\Nthe bathroom right after Tokitsu left for his room,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.28,1:12:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nor Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who went to get cigarettes\Nfrom his room thirty minutes later, could do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.33,1:12:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the one who went looking for him just\Nbefore Tokitsu was ready to demonstrate his locked room,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.42,1:12:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're the only one who could be the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.54,1:12:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.38,1:12:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When will you ever stop disappointing me?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.80,1:12:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but he didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.35,1:12:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because the real sinner is the one who was\Nable to open and close the lock with a single wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.98,1:12:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.94,1:12:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person is you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.48,1:12:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What kinda of dumb...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.57,1:12:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pretended to leave to get your cigarettes and\Ninstead went to the shed and forced open the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.41,1:12:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The padlock had been tossed into the\Nshed, wet, with fresh pick marks on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.29,1:12:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it was picked by the one who\Nwent outside after it began to rain: Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.96,1:12:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, the toolbox in your\Nroom is the only one without a wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.09,1:12:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how did he get into the locked room?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.34,1:13:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came here three days ago to check the place out, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.93,1:13:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably at that time he made a small hole in the window of the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.06,1:13:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And tonight, after murdering\NTokitsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, he went outside through the window,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.40,1:13:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And used the wire to lock it through\Nthe hole in the glass he made before.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.86,1:13:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, because of Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s carelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.78,1:13:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He smashed the window glass to pieces to get into the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.08,1:13:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you anticipated, this hid the hole already made in the glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.46,1:13:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, breaking the radio in the shed was to make us all\Nuneasy and drive us into believing another person might be murdered.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.76,1:13:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.05,1:13:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That's...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.39,1:13:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.10,1:13:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he could predict that\NHeiji-niichan would smash the window glass,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.15,1:13:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't know which of the four panes he would break.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.02,1:14:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's more, no matter how hot-blooded Heiji-niichan\Nmay be, if there was a hole, I think he would have noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.78,1:14:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Adding "hot-blooded" wasn't necessary...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.95,1:14:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure he's the one who picked the padlock on the shed!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.16,1:14:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think it's pretty likely this guy just a lousy thief.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.87,1:14:20.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But so what? In your head, does being a thief\Nautomatically equate to him being the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.72,1:14:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it is for me...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.76,1:14:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, do you know how the locked room trick done?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.68,1:14:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, it was a really simple trick!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.31,1:14:34.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you undo the screws that hold the\Nwindow frame in place, leaving the window alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.06,1:14:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The setup is "OK" when the all the pulled out screws are cut by pliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.02,1:14:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you reinsert the cut screws in the frame, fasten the edges\Nof the frame with glue, and fit the entire window back in from outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.20,1:14:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, even though outwardly it\Nappears to be fastened, the screws are too short.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.04,1:14:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're done, the window is attached only because of the glue.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.38,1:14:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you see, the one who-
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.77,1:14:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.21,1:15:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the one who happened to be the\Nlast to go to Tokitsu's room, Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.68,1:15:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must've been you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.09,1:15:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about, Heiji-niichan? That guy...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.76,1:15:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the chance when Tokitsu was working carefully,\Nimmersed in creating the trick, to attack and murder him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.69,1:15:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to interrupt your speech, but why would Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.19,1:15:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.90,1:15:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this in Tokitsu's room...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.86,1:15:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This screw with it's head cut off.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.03,1:15:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This guy...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.41,1:15:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.30,1:15:44.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,How about it? This is conclusive proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.75,1:15:44.15,Xtitle02,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\3c&H329122&\bord1\blur4}Green\NMessage from Heiji
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.59,1:15:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess you couldn't collect them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.76,1:15:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, when you used the pliers to cut the\Nscrews, you couldn't know where they would fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.44,1:16:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.98,1:16:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it was you... the one who killed Tokitsu.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.03,1:16:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.62,1:16:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason Tokitsu said it would take an hour to\Nprepare was because he had to wait for the glue to dry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.46,1:16:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how quickly he could unfasten and cut the screws,\Neven a quick drying glue would take at least thirty minutes to dry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.51,1:16:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means Tokitsu finished in less than thirty\Nminutes and was planning to wait outside the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.56,1:16:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, the murderer went to kill him while he still was in his room,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.69,1:16:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning it had to be you because you\Nleft your seat just as we started dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.32,1:16:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you pretended to go to the\Nbathroom and went to Tokitsu's room instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.44,1:16:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must've said "I figured out the locked room trick, can\Nwe compare solutions?" to get inside and beat him to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.45,1:17:01.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that you completed the trick and made it a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.50,1:17:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you entered through the main door, and\Nreturned to the dining room pretending to know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.17,1:17:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, this story is just my\Nhypothesis about what you could have done.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.55,1:17:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.30,1:17:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I took this screw from the radio in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.85,1:17:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking you got them all, you got nervous, thinking you missed one.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.56,1:17:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, thinking we suspected Kouya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you tried to\Ntake the chance and look where you were hiding them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.41,1:17:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would have thought you'd carry them in\Nyour pocket and keep fumbling around with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.33,1:17:44.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.96,1:17:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I expected you to at least have the one you\Npicked up when pretending to be scared of thunder.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.80,1:17:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew we would check the shed.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.30,1:18:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proof is that you were looking outside next.\Nto the window without being scared of the thunder.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.98,1:18:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, you crouched down in order to\Npick up a screw that you had missed before.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.19,1:18:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.07,1:18:13.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have been...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.95,1:18:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your ears are pierced.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.70,1:18:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You blocked your ears then to hide that, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.79,1:18:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pierced?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.87,1:18:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.25,1:18:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you were wearing headphones on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.96,1:18:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if the sea breeze blew your hair, we'd see them.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.88,1:18:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, in England, students with earrings\Nare everywhere, so I would've missed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.51,1:18:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I remember you mentioning the school's strict\Nregulations, meaning you can't wear pierced earrings, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.89,1:18:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.06,1:18:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm already 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.64,1:18:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I graduated from high school two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.60,1:18:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I brought my old uniform so I\Nwouldn't be exposed, but that was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.15,1:18:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd seem like a schoolgirl if I talked about school regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.61,1:18:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did you do this?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.74,1:19:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you gather us high-school detectives here?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.46,1:19:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was something I wanted to discover.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.67,1:19:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.29,1:19:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Lavender Mansion Locked Room Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.05,1:19:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to find the high-school detective that solved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.84,1:19:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean it was Tokitsu?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.35,1:19:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The newspapers didn't include the name or details of the case.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.73,1:19:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that guy just randomly stopped\Nby the mansion on his trip to Shikoku,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.15,1:19:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Solved the locked room murder, and left without leaving his name.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.57,1:19:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to that, my close friend, who,was a housekeeper at the mansion,\Nfell under suspicion since she had been alone with the young mistress.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.87,1:19:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the mansion as well, as a\Ndetective, one month before that guy appeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.42,1:19:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My friend asked me to investigate\Nwhether it might have been a murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.14,1:20:08.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.85,1:20:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only conclusion I could come to was that she\Nhad closed herself in her room and committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.11,1:20:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.53,1:20:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did your friend become a suspect?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.70,1:20:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One month later, that high-school detective found them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.20,1:20:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Screws with their heads cut off scattered outside of\Nher room. The window had been fastened by glue as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.92,1:20:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you have overlooked it?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.42,1:20:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't overlook it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.13,1:20:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Tsuchio guy turned up dressed as\Na cleaning contractor and setup the trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.31,1:20:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably only unfastened the window so he could rob them later.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.60,1:20:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why your expression changed when the Lavender\NMansion was mentioned and you tried to get away from the island.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.78,1:21:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Half a year after the case, Tokitsu bit into that trick, and displayed his\Ndeductive powers by telling the police and the media it was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.00,1:21:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had checked the corrosion on those\Nscattered screws, he should have known.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.92,1:21:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Tokitsu had been bothered\Nby that, and didn't disclose his name.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.14,1:21:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I didn't know where the high-school detective was from.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.60,1:21:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My only clue was the message my\Nfriend left on the phone before she passed on.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.11,1:21:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high-school detective with a weird accent is suspecting me!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.03,1:21:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.03,1:21:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help me, Natsuki!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.74,1:21:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those were her words.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.54,1:21:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, someone who spoke strangely.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.75,1:22:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been studying abroad for a long\Ntime, so I've been neglecting my Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.63,1:22:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} has a broad Kansai accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.88,1:22:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Tokitsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} used "this one" to refer to himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.30,1:22:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and not to mention, you three were the only\Nhigh-school detectives that have influence with the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.81,1:22:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Kudou wasn't on your list from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.19,1:22:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.50,1:22:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, he's quite popular though, so I just\Nused his name for the call to Hakuba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.32,1:22:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after gathering us detectives at this lodge,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.49,1:22:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First after putting Tsuchio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to sleep and tying him up, you used the\Nsame locked room trick from Lavender Mansion case to find your target.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.75,1:22:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.04,1:22:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I left the necessary tools in the rooms,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.05,1:22:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And filled the place with the smell of lavender.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.59,1:22:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That high-school detective should\Nrecall the case right away and figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.02,1:22:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mansion was so full of lavender flowers...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.31,1:23:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right? You worked as a\Nbutler there after all, Kouya Renzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.45,1:23:06.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.16,1:23:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was very fond of the young mistress.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.45,1:23:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young mistress!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.96,1:23:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did you bring him here?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.34,1:23:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he knew the young mistress\Nplanned to commit suicide, but he kept quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.05,1:23:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.18,1:23:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young mistress, your medicine!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.60,1:23:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop! Leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.18,1:23:35.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could not say anything...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.27,1:23:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would dishonor the young mistress.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.44,1:23:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought any doubts about her would soon clear up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.61,1:23:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never thought that would happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.61,1:23:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am truly sorry!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.70,1:23:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But hey, hold on...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.91,1:23:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you brought those two here because you hated them...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.29,1:23:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no rescue ship is going to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.38,1:24:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told that ship's captain if he didn't keep it\Nsecret, he wouldn't get the rest of his money.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.22,1:24:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never intended to leave here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.13,1:24:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I considered the possibility that my\Nopponent might figure out my intentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.85,1:24:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tokitsu bragged about his incorrect Lavender\NMansion deduction right up until I bashed his head in.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.31,1:24:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a worthless guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.44,1:24:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the one who broke the radio...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.90,1:24:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it was me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.24,1:24:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll all die here together.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.70,1:24:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.08,1:24:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.62,1:24:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be rescued.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.46,1:24:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.79,1:24:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.21,1:24:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you came half a day ahead of us, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.01,1:24:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't come on your own cruiser or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.72,1:24:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I just arrived at the harbor earlier than I planned.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.31,1:25:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked about a seldom used lodge where\Na large number of people were going to stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.44,1:25:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And looked for a ship that had brought food and\Nfuel to a deserted island, and had it bring me here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.61,1:25:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For an appropriate fee.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.78,1:25:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean no one knows you came here?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.95,1:25:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.78,1:25:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't tell anyone either?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.37,1:25:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I did tell someone, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.83,1:25:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's kinda slow.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.96,1:25:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.67,1:25:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sound...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.63,1:25:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.01,1:25:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the generator broke.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.72,1:25:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the sound of the generator.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.14,1:25:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That means, that sound is...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.10,1:25:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.27,1:25:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.03,1:25:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.61,1:25:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha brought us a boat!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.03,1:25:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.20,1:25:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji-niichan left behind a message and a marker.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.12,1:25:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I won't fall behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.54,1:26:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori Heiji is here!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.46,1:26:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I can see Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.26,1:26:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} too!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.55,1:26:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.64,1:26:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.35,1:26:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, if you'd have just been frank with me, I\Nwouldn't have had to give you five judo throws.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.35,1:26:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was six, actually...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.98,1:26:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.48,1:26:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.86,1:26:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they exist...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.23,1:26:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot-blooded detectives like you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.61,1:26:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Busting down a door over a\Nbloodstained knob or breaking in through the glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.74,1:26:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I put the body against the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.75,1:26:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you rammed your way in and\Ndisconnected the window, I would have been found out.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.83,1:26:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, because you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.21,1:26:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm hot blooded.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.75,1:26:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The right thing is...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.17,1:26:54.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To have faith in life, until you're sure of death.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.05,1:26:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what makes a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.01,1:26:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.06,1:27:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If God ever forgives me...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.73,1:27:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd love to do a real Detective Koushien...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.11,1:27:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.66,1:27:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And return to the days when I called myself 'boku'.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.20,1:28:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he? Is he? Is Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} there?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.00,1:28:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't see him!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.63,1:28:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm right here.
